NLquery: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them.
prompt: Translate this natural language query into SQL format: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them.
LLM_returned_SQL_query:
SELECT
    bm.sid,
    bm.version
FROM (
    -- Count how many times each (sid, version) pair appears
    SELECT
        sid,
        version,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY sid
            ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC
        ) AS rn
    FROM BaseModel
    GROUP BY sid, version
) AS bm
WHERE bm.rn = 1;

NLquery: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them.
prompt:
CREATE TABLE ModelServices (
    bmid INT NOT NULL,
    sid INT NOT NULL,
    version INT NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (bmid, sid),
    FOREIGN KEY (bmid) REFERENCES BaseModel(bmid) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    FOREIGN KEY (sid) REFERENCES InternetService(sid) ON DELETE CASCADE
);

Translate this natural language query into SQL format: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them.
LLM_returned_SQL_query:
SELECT ms.sid, ms.version
FROM ModelServices ms
JOIN (
    SELECT sid, version, 
           ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
               PARTITION BY sid 
               ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC
           ) AS rn
    FROM ModelServices
    GROUP BY sid, version
) ranked
ON ms.sid = ranked.sid AND ms.version = ranked.version
WHERE ranked.rn = 1;

Translate this natural language query into MySQL format: For each Internet Service(sid), find the most frequently used version among all Base Models that utilize it. If multiple versions have the same highest frequency, you may return any one of them.
LLM_returned_SQL_query:
SELECT sid, version
FROM (
    SELECT 
        sid,
        version,
        COUNT(*) AS freq,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY sid ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC) AS rn
    FROM ModelServices
    GROUP BY sid, version
) AS t
WHERE rn = 1;

NLquery: Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh.
prompt: Translate this natural language query into SQL format: Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh.
LLM_returned_SQL_query:
SELECT u.sid
FROM Utilizes u
JOIN BaseModel b ON u.bid = b.bid
WHERE b.creator = 'user_iuwrh'
GROUP BY u.sid
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT u.bid) = (
    SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT bid)
    FROM BaseModel
    WHERE creator = 'user_iuwrh'
);

NLquery: Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh.
prompt:
CREATE TABLE User (
    uid INT,
    email TEXT NOT NULL,
    username TEXT NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (uid)
);

CREATE TABLE AgentCreator (
    uid INT,
    bio TEXT,
    payout TEXT,
    PRIMARY KEY (uid),
    FOREIGN KEY (uid) REFERENCES User(uid) ON DELETE CASCADE
);

CREATE TABLE ModelServices (
    bmid INT NOT NULL,
    sid INT NOT NULL,
    version INT NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (bmid, sid),
    FOREIGN KEY (bmid) REFERENCES BaseModel(bmid) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    FOREIGN KEY (sid) REFERENCES InternetService(sid) ON DELETE CASCADE
);

CREATE TABLE BaseModel (
    bmid INT,
    creator_uid INT NOT NULL,
    description TEXT NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (bmid),
    FOREIGN KEY (creator_uid) REFERENCES AgentCreator(uid) ON DELETE CASCADE
);

Translate this natural language query into MySQL format: Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh.
LLM_returned_SQL_query:
SELECT ms.sid
FROM ModelServices ms
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM BaseModel bm
    JOIN AgentCreator ac ON bm.creator_uid = ac.uid
    JOIN User u ON u.uid = ac.uid
    WHERE u.username = 'user_iuwrh'
      AND NOT EXISTS (
          SELECT 1
          FROM ModelServices ms2
          WHERE ms2.bmid = bm.bmid
            AND ms2.sid = ms.sid
      )
);

NLquery: Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by every Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh.
prompt:

    uid INT,
    email TEXT NOT NULL,
    username TEXT NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (uid)
);

CREATE TABLE AgentCreator (
    uid INT,
    bio TEXT,
    payout TEXT,
    PRIMARY KEY (uid),
    FOREIGN KEY (uid) REFERENCES User(uid) ON DELETE CASCADE
);

CREATE TABLE ModelServices (
    bmid INT NOT NULL,
    sid INT NOT NULL,
    version INT NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (bmid, sid),
    FOREIGN KEY (bmid) REFERENCES BaseModel(bmid) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    FOREIGN KEY (sid) REFERENCES InternetService(sid) ON DELETE CASCADE
);

CREATE TABLE BaseModel (
    bmid INT,
    creator_uid INT NOT NULL,
    description TEXT NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (bmid),
    FOREIGN KEY (creator_uid) REFERENCES AgentCreator(uid) ON DELETE CASCADE
);

Translate this natural language query into MySQL format: Find all the Internet Service(sid) that are utilized by any Base Model built by the agent creator user_iuwrh.
LLM_returned_SQL_query:
SELECT DISTINCT ms.sid
FROM User u
JOIN AgentCreator ac ON ac.uid = u.uid
JOIN BaseModel bm ON bm.creator_uid = ac.uid
JOIN ModelServices ms ON ms.bmid = bm.bmid
WHERE u.username = 'user_iuwrh';

NLquery: Find all customized models(mid) that do not appear in model configurations.
prompt:
CREATE TABLE ModelConfigurations (
    bmid INT NOT NULL,
    mid INT NOT NULL,
    cid INT NOT NULL,
    duration INT NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (bmid, mid, cid),
    FOREIGN KEY (bmid, mid) REFERENCES CustomizedModel(bmid, mid) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    FOREIGN KEY (cid) REFERENCES Configuration(cid) ON DELETE CASCADE
);

Translate this natural language query into MySQL format: Find all customized models(mid) that do not appear in model configurations.
LLM_returned_SQL_query:
SELECT cm.mid
FROM CustomizedModel AS cm
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
    SELECT 1
    FROM ModelConfigurations AS mc
    WHERE mc.bmid = cm.bmid
      AND mc.mid = cm.mid
);

NLquery: Find all customized models(mid) that do not appear in model configurations.
prompt:
CREATE TABLE CustomizedModel (
    bmid INT,
    mid INT NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (bmid, mid),
    FOREIGN KEY (bmid) REFERENCES BaseModel(bmid) ON DELETE CASCADE
);

CREATE TABLE ModelConfigurations (
    bmid INT NOT NULL,
    mid INT NOT NULL,
    cid INT NOT NULL,
    duration INT NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (bmid, mid, cid),
    FOREIGN KEY (bmid, mid) REFERENCES CustomizedModel(bmid, mid) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    FOREIGN KEY (cid) REFERENCES Configuration(cid) ON DELETE CASCADE
);

CREATE TABLE BaseModel (
    bmid INT,
    creator_uid INT NOT NULL,
    description TEXT NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (bmid),
    FOREIGN KEY (creator_uid) REFERENCES AgentCreator(uid) ON DELETE CASCADE
);

Translate this natural language query into MySQL format: Find all customized models(mid) that do not appear in model configurations.
LLM_returned_SQL_query:
SELECT cm.mid
FROM CustomizedModel AS cm
LEFT JOIN ModelConfigurations AS mc
    ON cm.bmid = mc.bmid
   AND cm.mid = mc.mid
WHERE mc.mid IS NULL;
